The '''Lompobattang flycatcher''' ('''''Ficedula bonthaina'''''), also spelt '''Lompobatang flycatcher''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Muscicapidae]]. It is [[endemic]] to the [[Indonesia]] island of [[Sulawesi]]. Its natural [[habitat]] is subtropical or tropical moist [[montane forest]]s. It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].

